			<td class="BoardRowA">
			<a class="AuthorLink" href="/user.asp?usr=19063">Emay</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;			
			</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA">4/26/00 8:39pm</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA"><a name="5521893"><span style="font-weight: bold;">
				And so it begins
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Emay awoke from his slumber, that was given to him by The Nameless. <br>  <br> He knelt down in humility and started to pray. <br>  <br> &quot;Lord, what must I do first to begin my journey.&quot; <br>  <br> He felt the Spirit of the Nameless come to him.  The following words Emay heard in his mind- <br>  <br> &lt;i&gt;Go to the city of Qeynos.  One of my tenders in human guise shall help you with your quest there.&lt;/i&gt; <br>  <br> &quot;Your will be done Lord.&quot; <br>  <br> Emay quickly got up, and made his way to the Erudin docks.  Within a few moments the boat to Qeynos arrived at there, and Emay got on the small boat that lead up to it. <br>  <br> The boat started on it's journey to Qeynos when the sky started to cloud over, soon there was a fierce storm. <br>  <br> The captain started to shout commands to his crew, hoping against all odds to keep the ship afloat. <br>  <br> Emay looked at the anarchy that was going all around him, and he started to doubt.  Emay went on his knees afraid for his life.  He felt the spirit of the nameless come to him and it gave him strength.  He went into the midst of the ship, where everybody could see him. <br>  <br> &quot;Nameless, thou saith that no foe would ever defeat me, but this storm has come up and if thou doesn't stop it I shall perish by drowning.  Save me.&quot; <br>  <br> &lt;i&gt;As you wish my son&lt;/i&gt; <br>  <br> The storm almost immediately stopped and the clouds started to disappear. <br>  <br> The captain and the crew looked at Emay. <br>  <br> &quot;What did you do?  Never have I seen such magics used.  Not even a grand master druid - one who controls the powers of nature - could have stopped that storm.  Only one touched by the gods could do such a thing.  Which god touched you?&quot; The captain asked. <br>  <br> Emay got up, and through the spirit of the nameless testified onto the people. <br>  <br> &quot;I was not touched by the one who says- I am the one who created all the stars, all the worlds, and all those you call Gods- I am touched by the Nameless creator.&quot; Emay said with confidence. <br>  <br> &quot;I have never heard of such a thing.  When a person is touched by a God, they are here to tell us what that God wishes, what does the Nameless creator wish of us?&quot; one crew member asked. <br>  <br> &quot;He wishes you to repent, to stop following and worshiping the ones you call Gods, and to worship him.  He wants you to love him with all your heart, all your spirt, all your soul, and all your body.  He wants you also to love one another as you love thyself.&quot; Emay spoke, as the Nameless told him. <br>  <br> And the Captain, and the a few of the crew who felt the presence of the Nameless amongst them fell to their knees, and they repented of worshiping the false gods that they had been worshiping, and they gave their lives to the nameless. <br>  <br> Emay was sadden by those who didn't.  He quietly prayed to the Nameless - &quot;Lord why some repent and some did not?&quot; <br>  <br> &lt;i&gt;All you need to know my son is this - Testify to all what I have told you, those who hear and believe and repent shall be saved, those who do not believe are damned&lt;/i&gt; <br>  <br> &quot;Thy will be done Lord.&quot; Emay said in humility to the Nameless. <br>  <br> &quot;Emay what must we do?&quot; the Captain and crew asked. <br>  <br> The spirit of the nameless came onto Emay and he did speak what the nameless said onto him- <br>  <br> &quot;Go out and teach all the world to repent of worshiping the false gods that the Nameless created to tend over the world - to love the Nameless with all your heart, all your spirit, all your soul, and all your body, and to Love one another as you love thyself.  Those who believe and repent shall be saved, those who hear and believe not shall be damned.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;We shall great teacher.&quot; all those who repented said unto Emay. <br>  <br> Emay left the boat and was greeted by a young boy. <br>  <br> &quot;Hello sir, I really need your help.&quot; <br>  <br> Emay looked at the young boy, and stood there for a few seconds.  He had been sent by the nameless to find one of his tenders that would lead him on the way to his quest.  But he remembered the words of the nameless very well- to love thy neighbor as you love thyself. <br>  <br> &quot;Thy will be done Nameless.&quot; Emay said under his breath. <br>  <br> Emay turned to the young boy. <br>  <br> &quot;Young one, what is it that you need my help for?&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;I'm a poor beggar sir- bandits captured me, my Mother lives in Freeport, and I need to go there.&quot; <br>  <br> Emay looked at him.  This would prove a major detour on his journey.  But he had to go to all the ends of the world, to all the cities in Norrath and preach the word of the Nameless.  Might as well start in Freeport- across the great continent. <br>  <br> &quot;Yes young boy, I can take you to Freeport.  Let us both pray for a safe journey, for the journey is dangerous.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;Which god should we pray to?&quot; the young boy asked. <br>  <br> &quot;Not to any of those who you know as Gods- but to the one who says - I am he who created the stars, the planets, and all those who you call gods - we pray to the nameless.&quot; <br>  <br> Instantly the young boy turned into a normal sized human.  An illusion. <br>  <br> &quot;I am the tender sent to help you on your journey Emay.  I was told to test you by the Nameless, to appear to you first as a young boy, and after you passed the test to appear as a man- as the scripture foretold.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;What scripture?&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;The word of the Nameless.  I am here to give it to you, and you shall tell all those in Norrath about the great news that is found there in.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;Blessed be the Nameless.&quot; <br>  <br> In the man's hand appeared a book.  He handed it to Emay. <br>  <br> &quot;Thank you.  What must I do here to bring the people of Qeynos to the Nameless.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;You must defeat the Necromancer Guild and Corporal Lancot- for they use the forbidden arts of the dead- which is an abomination to the Nameless.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;Thy will be done Nameless.&quot; Emay said. <br>  <br> End of Part 2		

